li.code:
Prior to this fix, the following code:
 EntityManager em = emf.getEntityManager();
 lookupJTATransaction().begin();
 em.persist(newEntity);
 lookupJTATransaction().commit();

EclipseLink would incorrectly register with the active transaction when persist was called, and flush when the transaction commits.  With this fix, the entityManager no longer registers with the transaction, and so nothing will get written out.  The specification requires that joinTransaction be called when the transaction is started after obtaining a user managed EM:

 EntityManager em = emf.getEntityManager();
 lookupJTATransaction().begin();
 em.joinTransaction(); //this is required for em to participate in the transaction
 em.persist(newEntity);
 lookupJTATransaction().commit();

Without the joinTransaction call, the insert will not happen, and any EntityManager calls requiring a transaction will result in a TransactionRequiredException "Cannot call methods requiring a transaction if the entity manager has not been joined to the current transaction.".
